Package org.forgerock.openam.idrepo.ldap.psearch

Class DJLDAPv3PersistentSearch

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.iplanet.services.ldap.event.LDAPv3PersistentSearch<IdRepoListener,​Set<IdType>>
      • org.forgerock.openam.idrepo.ldap.psearch.DJLDAPv3PersistentSearch
  • public class DJLDAPv3PersistentSearch
extends LDAPv3PersistentSearch<IdRepoListener,​Set<IdType>>
    This class will execute persistent search request against the configured datastore. When a result is received, the internal caches will be notified about the changes, so the caches can be dirtied.

      • DJLDAPv3PersistentSearch

        public DJLDAPv3PersistentSearch​(Map<String,​Set<String>> configMap,
                                ConnectionFactory factory)
        Creates a new DJLDAPv3PersistentSearch using the provided configuration data and connection factory.
        Parameters:
        configMap - Non null. Map containing the configuration data necessary to perform a persistent search, including the retry interval, search DN, the filter to apply and scope of the query and any user attributes that will be returned through the connection.
        factory - Used to produce connections down to the LDAP datastore.

    • Method Detail

      • addMovedOrRenamedListener

        public void addMovedOrRenamedListener​(IdentityMovedOrRenamedListener movedOrRenamedListener)
        Adds an IdentityMovedOrRenamedListener object, which needs to be notified about persistent search results where the identity has been renamed or moved. The caller must ensure that calls to addMovedOrRenamedListener/removeMovedOrRenamedListener invocations are synchronized correctly.
        Parameters:
        movedOrRenamedListener - The IdentityMovedOrRenamedListener instance that needs to be notified about changes.

      • removeMovedOrRenamedListener

        public void removeMovedOrRenamedListener​(IdentityMovedOrRenamedListener movedOrRenamedListener)
        Removes an IdentityMovedOrRenamedListener if it was registered to get persistent search notifications. The caller must ensure that calls to addMovedOrRenamedListener/removeMovedOrRenamedListener invocations are synchronized correctly.
        Parameters:
        movedOrRenamedListener - The IdentityMovedOrRenamedListener instance to remove from the listeners
